<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-05-11T08:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-05-11T08:30:00-05:00" n="671" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d671">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79620 Boeing Airplane Co./25:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gade</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-11T10:00:00-03:30"><hi rend="italic">May 11,
                                            1928—10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 10:55
                                    a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>15. Department’s telegram 2 of February 6, 6 p.m.<note n="10" xml:id="d671fn10">See footnote 96, <ref target="#pg_820">p.
                                        820</ref>.</note> Military aviation authorities here report
                                this morning Captain O’Neill and companion in Comet aeroplane
                                crashed near Minas last night. Latest information affirms injuries
                                to both aviators slight.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gade</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>